	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Mbizana - President Jacob Zuma has extended get well wishes to the 58 victims of a bus accident that took place on Friday near Mbizana in the Eastern Cape. The passengers were involved in the accident while en route to OR Tambo Centenary national celebrations, where President Zuma officiated and addressed the community.“We send good wishes to the victims who were on their way to celebrate with us this momentous occasion to honour the legacy and life of the liberation struggle icon, African humanist and the longest serving President of the governing party, Mr Oliver Reginald Tambo. Our thoughts and prayers are with them and we wish the injured speedy recovery,” said President Zuma 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  